Class Image

  word.w2004.elements.Image
All Implemented Interfaces:
IElement, IFluentElement<Image>, IImage
public class Image
extends java.lang.Object
implements IImage, IFluentElement<Image>

Author:
leonardo Use this class when you want to add images to your document. You can insert images inside Paragraphs, Tables, Headings, Header, Footer and obviously, at the body of a Document.

getContent

public java.lang.String getContent()
Description copied from interface: IElement

This method returns the content (XML or HTML) of the Element and the content.

If you are using W2004, the return will be the XML required to generate the element.

Important: Once you call this method, the Document value is cached an no elements can be added later.

Specified by:
getContent in interface IElement
Returns:
this is the String value of the element ready to be appended/inserted in the Document.
